      • getReceipt_sms

        public java.lang.String getReceipt_sms()
        Returns:
        The mobile number to send this charge’s receipt to. The receipt will not be sent until the charge is paid. If this charge is for a customer, the mobile number specified here will override the customer’s mobile number. Receipts will not be sent for test mode charges. If receipt_sms is specified for a charge in live mode, a receipt will be sent regardless of your sms settings. (optional, either receipt_sms or receipt_email is required if customer is not available)

      • getReceipt_number

      • isRefunded

      • getSource

        public SourceResponse getSource()
        Returns:
        The source of every charge is a credit or debit card. This hash is then the card object describing that card.
        If source is null then, default Tap payment page link will be provided.
        if source.id = "src_kw.knet" then KNET payment page link will be provided.
        if source.id = "src_visamastercard" then Credit Card payment page link will be provided.
